1.11
log
@upgrade libxml and fold python flavour into main, since it was on by
default anyway, and, while I hate compiling this huge crap, less flavours
are actually a good thing (bsiegert@@ removed python's flavours too...)

while here, make it use the python module, and, as such, no longer
hard-code the use of python 2.3
@
text
@# $MirOS: ports/meta/gnome2/Makefile,v 1.10 2008/06/25 18:40:48 bsiegert Exp $

COMMENT=		meta package to install all of GNOME 2
VERSION=		2.18.2
DASH_VER=		2
PKGNAME=		meta-gnome2-${VERSION}-${DASH_VER}
CATEGORIES=		meta x11/gnome
HOMEPAGE=		http://www.gnome.org/
RESPONSIBLE=		Benny Siegert <bsiegert@@gmx.de>

DISTFILES=		

# GPL/LGPL
PERMIT_PACKAGE_CDROM=   Yes
PERMIT_PACKAGE_FTP=     Yes
PERMIT_DISTFILES_CDROM= Yes
PERMIT_DISTFILES_FTP=   Yes

NO_CHECKSUM=		Yes
NO_BUILD=		Yes
PLIST=			/dev/null
PKG_ARCH=		*
USE_X11=		Yes # GNOME needs X11
USE_CXX=		Yes # multiple dependencies use CXX

B_R_DEPENDS+=		:libxml->=2.6.32:textproc/libxml
